<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head', { pageTitle: 'About', pageDescription: 'Full-stack developer focused on SaaS products, AI tools, and solving real problems.' }) %>
</head>
<body>

  <%- include('partials/nav', { activePage: 'about' }) %>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="about-page__intro">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="hero__eyebrow reveal">About</p>
      <p class="about-page__lead reveal">
        I'm a full-stack developer with a product mindset — I don't just build
        what's asked, I ask what should be built, and why it matters.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Body -->
  <section class="section about-page">
    <div class="container about__inner">
      <div class="about__text reveal">
        <p class="about__body">
          My focus is on SaaS tools and AI-augmented workflows that solve
          specific, painful problems. I care more about whether something
          actually gets used than how many features it has.
        </p>
        <p class="about__body">
          Most of my work falls into one of two buckets: products I build for
          myself because I have the problem firsthand, and freelance projects
          where a client needs something custom-built rather than
          stitched together from templates.
        </p>
        <p class="about__body">
          Every project gets the same level of attention regardless of size —
          clean architecture, considered UX, and a working product at the end.
          No half-finished demos.
        </p>
        <p class="about__body">
          Currently building in public while taking on a small number of
          freelance clients. If you're working on something real, let's talk.
        </p>

        <div class="about__tags">
          <span class="tag">SaaS Architecture</span>
          <span class="tag">AI Integration</span>
          <span class="tag">Full-Stack</span>
          <span class="tag">Product Strategy</span>
          <span class="tag">TypeScript</span>
          <span class="tag">Node.js</span>
          <span class="tag">Next.js</span>
          <span class="tag">PostgreSQL</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about__aside reveal">
        <div class="about__stat-card">
          <div class="about__stat">
            <span class="stat__number">1+</span>
            <span class="stat__label">Years building software</span>
          </div>
          <div class="about__stat">
            <span class="stat__number">3+</span>
            <span class="stat__label">Products shipped</span>
          </div>
          <div class="about__stat">
            <span class="stat__number">1</span>
            <span class="stat__label">SaaS tools in production</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How I work -->
  <section class="section how-i-work">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section__header reveal">
        <p class="section__label">Approach</p>
        <h2 class="section__title">How I work.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="case-list">
        <div class="case-item reveal">
          <div class="case-item__header">
            <div class="case-item__meta">
              <span class="case-item__index">01</span>
              <h3 class="case-item__title">Scope tight, ship fast</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-item__body">
            <div class="case-block">
              <p class="case-block__text">
                I'd rather ship a focused v1 in two weeks than spend two
                months building something nobody's used yet. Real feedback
                beats imagined requirements.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-item reveal">
          <div class="case-item__header">
            <div class="case-item__meta">
              <span class="case-item__index">02</span>
              <h3 class="case-item__title">Clear communication</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-item__body">
            <div class="case-block">
              <p class="case-block__text">
                For client work, that means regular updates, honest timelines,
                and flagging problems early — not after they've become
                expensive.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="case-item reveal">
          <div class="case-item__header">
            <div class="case-item__meta">
              <span class="case-item__index">03</span>
              <h3 class="case-item__title">Built to last</h3>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="case-item__body">
            <div class="case-block">
              <p class="case-block__text">
                Fast doesn't mean sloppy. Clean code, sensible architecture,
                and documentation that means the next person (or future me)
                isn't lost.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section cta-band">
    <div class="container cta-band__inner reveal">
      <h2 class="cta-band__title">Want to work together?</h2>
      <p class="cta-band__sub">I'm open to freelance projects and early-stage SaaS collaborations.</p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn--primary">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/footer') %>

  <script src="/assets/js/animations.js"></script>
  <script src="/assets/js/navigation.js"></script>
  <script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      initAnimations();
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>
